{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":639,"text":"So this is a picture of my dad and me,\nat the beach in Far Rockaway,"},{"time":7178,"text":"or actually Rockaway Park."},{"time":8664,"text":"I'm the one with the blond hair."},{"time":11354,"text":"My dad's the guy with the cigarette."},{"time":13320,"text":"It was the 60's."},{"time":14495,"text":"A lot of people smoked back then."},{"time":16157,"text":"In the summer of 2009,\nmy dad was diagnosed with lung cancer."},{"time":22302,"text":"Cancer is one of those things\nthat actually touches everybody."},{"time":26049,"text":"If you're a man in the US,"},{"time":28701,"text":"you've got about a one in two chance"},{"time":30771,"text":"of being diagnosed with cancer\nduring your lifetime."},{"time":33730,"text":"If you're a woman, you've got\nabout a one in three chance"},{"time":36539,"text":"of being diagnosed with cancer."},{"time":39025,"text":"Everybody knows somebody\nwho's been diagnosed with cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43355,"text":"Now, my dad's doing better today,"},{"time":44959,"text":"and part of the reason for that is that\nhe was able to participate in the trial"},{"time":50016,"text":"of an experimental new drug\nthat happened to be specially formulated"},{"time":53273,"text":"and very good for his particular\nkind of cancer."},{"time":55550,"text":"There are over 200 kinds of cancer."},{"time":58660,"text":"And what I want to talk about today"},{"time":60944,"text":"is how we can help\nmore people like my dad,"},{"time":63840,"text":"because we have to change the way\nwe think about raising money"},{"time":66818,"text":"to fund cancer research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69273,"text":"So a while after my dad was diagnosed,"},{"time":71231,"text":"I was having coffee\nwith my friend Andrew Lo."},{"time":74407,"text":"He's the head of the Laboratory\nfor Financial Engineering at MIT,"},{"time":77697,"text":"where I also have a position,"},{"time":79659,"text":"and we were talking about cancer."},{"time":81285,"text":"And Andrew had been doing\nhis own bits of research,"},{"time":83703,"text":"and one of the things\nthat he had been told"},{"time":85821,"text":"and that he'd learned\nfrom studying the literature"},{"time":90290,"text":"was that there's actually\na big bottleneck."},{"time":92395,"text":"It's very difficult to develop new drugs,"},{"time":94559,"text":"and the reason it's difficult\nto develop new drugs"},{"time":96943,"text":"is because in the early stages\nof drug development,"},{"time":99388,"text":"the drugs are very risky,\nand they're very expensive."},{"time":101917,"text":"So Andrew asked me\nif I'd want to maybe work with him a bit,"},{"time":104814,"text":"work on some of the math and the analytics"},{"time":106948,"text":"and see if we could figure out\nsomething we could do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110116,"text":"Now I'm not a scientist."},{"time":111609,"text":"You know, I don't know\nhow to build a drug."},{"time":113681,"text":"And none of my coauthors, Andrew Lo\nor Jose-Maria Fernandez or David Fagnan --"},{"time":118600,"text":"none of those guys are scientists either."},{"time":121339,"text":"We don't know the first thing\nabout how to make a cancer drug."},{"time":124828,"text":"But we know a little bit\nabout risk mitigation"},{"time":127051,"text":"and a little bit\nabout financial engineering,"},{"time":129191,"text":"and so we started thinking,\nwhat could we do?"},{"time":132079,"text":"I'm going to tell you about some work"},{"time":133913,"text":"we've been doing\nover the last couple years"},{"time":136022,"text":"that we think could\nfundamentally change the way"},{"time":138317,"text":"research for cancer\nand lots of other things gets done."},{"time":141750,"text":"We want to let the research\ndrive the funding,"},{"time":144163,"text":"not the other way around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146446,"text":"So in order to get started,"},{"time":147764,"text":"let me tell you\nhow you get a drug financed."},{"time":149911,"text":"Imagine that you're in your lab --\nyou're a scientist, you're not like me --"},{"time":154336,"text":"and you've developed a new compound"},{"time":156332,"text":"that you think might be therapeutic\nfor somebody with cancer."},{"time":160212,"text":"Well, what you do is, you test in animals,\nyou test in test tubes,"},{"time":163892,"text":"but there's this notion\nof going from the bench to the bedside,"},{"time":166976,"text":"and in order to get from the bench,\nthe lab, to the bedside, to the patients,"},{"time":170652,"text":"you've got to get the drug tested."},{"time":172506,"text":"And the way the drug gets tested"},{"time":174134,"text":"is through a series of,\nbasically, experiments,"},{"time":176379,"text":"through these large,\nthey're called trials,"},{"time":178434,"text":"that they do to determine\nwhether the drug is safe"},{"time":180813,"text":"and whether it works and all these things."},{"time":182850,"text":"So the FDA has a very specific protocol."},{"time":184954,"text":"In the first phase of this testing,"},{"time":186669,"text":"which is called testing for toxicity,\nit's called Phase I."},{"time":190675,"text":"In the first phase,\nyou give the drug to healthy people"},{"time":193393,"text":"and you see if it actually\nmakes them sick."},{"time":196578,"text":"In other words, are the side\neffects just so severe"},{"time":198996,"text":"that no matter how much good it does,"},{"time":200808,"text":"it's not going to be worth it?"},{"time":202290,"text":"Does it cause heart attacks,\nkill people, liver failure?"},{"time":205005,"text":"And it turns out,\nthat's a pretty high hurdle."},{"time":207182,"text":"About a third of all drugs\ndrop out at that point."},{"time":209663,"text":"In the next phase, you test\nto see if the drug's effective,"},{"time":212546,"text":"and you give it to people with cancer"},{"time":214360,"text":"and you see if it makes them better."},{"time":216115,"text":"And that's also a higher hurdle.\nPeople drop out."},{"time":218457,"text":"And in the third phase,\nyou test it on a very large sample,"},{"time":221287,"text":"and you're trying to determine\nwhat the right dose is,"},{"time":224419,"text":"is it better than what's available today?\nIf not, then why build it?"},{"time":227891,"text":"When you're done with all that,"},{"time":229960,"text":"what you have is a very small\npercentage of drugs"},{"time":232469,"text":"that start the process\nactually come out the other side."},{"time":235319,"text":"So those blue bottles --\nthose blue bottles save lives,"},{"time":239057,"text":"and they're also worth billions,\nsometimes billions a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242800,"text":"So now here's a question:"},{"time":244399,"text":"if I were to ask you, for example,"},{"time":247665,"text":"to make a one-time investment of, say,\n200 million dollars"},{"time":251654,"text":"to buy one of those bottles,"},{"time":253322,"text":"so 200 million dollars up front, one time,\nto buy one of those bottles,"},{"time":256698,"text":"I won't tell you which one it is,"},{"time":258338,"text":"and in 10 years, I'll tell you whether\nyou have one of the blue ones."},{"time":262263,"text":"Does that sound like a good\ndeal for anybody?"},{"time":264418,"text":"No. No, right?"},{"time":265680,"text":"And of course, it's a very,\nvery risky trial position,"},{"time":268238,"text":"and that's why it's very hard\nto get funding,"},{"time":270404,"text":"but to a first approximation,\nthat's actually the proposal."},{"time":273224,"text":"You have to fund these things\nfrom the early stages on."},{"time":275858,"text":"It takes a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277149,"text":"So Andrew said to me, he said,"},{"time":280590,"text":"\"What if we stop thinking\nabout these as drugs?"},{"time":283060,"text":"What if we start thinking\nabout them as financial assets?\""},{"time":285870,"text":"They've got really weird payoff\nstructures and all that,"},{"time":288538,"text":"but let's throw everything we know\nabout financial engineering at them."},{"time":291902,"text":"Let's see if we can use\nall the tricks of the trade"},{"time":294386,"text":"to figure out how to make these drugs\nwork as financial assets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298344,"text":"Let's create a giant fund."},{"time":300289,"text":"In finance, we know what to do\nwith assets that are risky."},{"time":303057,"text":"You put them in a portfolio\nand you try to smooth out the returns."},{"time":306193,"text":"So we did some math, and it turned out\nyou could make this work,"},{"time":309260,"text":"but in order to make it work,\nyou need about 80 to 150 drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312716,"text":"Now the good news is,\nthere's plenty of drugs"},{"time":314905,"text":"that are waiting to be tested."},{"time":316389,"text":"We've been told that there's a backlog\nof about 20 years of drugs"},{"time":320346,"text":"that are waiting to be tested\nbut can't be funded."},{"time":322823,"text":"In fact, that early stage\nof the funding process,"},{"time":325244,"text":"that Phase I and preclinical stuff,"},{"time":327240,"text":"that's actually, in the industry,\ncalled the Valley of Death"},{"time":330133,"text":"because it's where drugs go to die."},{"time":331894,"text":"It's very hard to for them\nto get through there,"},{"time":334172,"text":"and of course, if you can't\nget through there,"},{"time":336423,"text":"you can't get to the later stages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338081,"text":"So we did this math,\nand we figured out, OK,"},{"time":340157,"text":"well, you need about 80 to, say, 150,\nor something like that, drugs."},{"time":343767,"text":"And then we did a little more\nmath, and we said, OK,"},{"time":346577,"text":"well, that's a fund of about three\nto 15 billion dollars."},{"time":349863,"text":"So we kind of created a new problem\nby solving the old one."},{"time":353905,"text":"We got rid of the risk,\nbut now we need a lot of capital,"},{"time":356612,"text":"and you can only get that kind\nof capital in the capital markets."},{"time":359747,"text":"Venture capitalists\nand philanthropies don't have it."},{"time":362264,"text":"But we have to figure out\nhow to get people in the capital markets,"},{"time":365495,"text":"who traditionally don't invest in this,\nto want to invest in this stuff."},{"time":369011,"text":"So again, financial engineering\nwas helpful here."},{"time":371353,"text":"Imagine the megafund starts empty,"},{"time":373177,"text":"and what it does is it issues\nsome debt and some equity,"},{"time":377210,"text":"and that generates cash flow."},{"time":378964,"text":"That cash flow is used, then, to buy\nthat big portfolio of drugs that you need,"},{"time":382733,"text":"and those drugs start working their way\nthrough that approval process,"},{"time":386070,"text":"and each time they go through\na phase of approval,"},{"time":388485,"text":"they gain value."},{"time":389704,"text":"Most of them don't make it,\nbut a few of them do,"},{"time":392086,"text":"and with the ones that gain\nvalue, you can sell some,"},{"time":394616,"text":"and when you sell them,"},{"time":395878,"text":"you have money to pay\nthe interest on those bonds,"},{"time":398240,"text":"but also to fund the next round of trials."},{"time":400315,"text":"It's almost self-funding."},{"time":401564,"text":"You do that for the course\nof the transaction,"},{"time":403868,"text":"and when you're done,\nyou liquidate the portfolio,"},{"time":406321,"text":"pay back the bonds, and you can give\nthe equity holders a nice return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409667,"text":"That was the theory,\nand we talked about it,"},{"time":411866,"text":"we did a bunch of experiments,"},{"time":413360,"text":"and then we said,\nlet's really try to test it."},{"time":415552,"text":"We spent the next two years\ndoing research."},{"time":418915,"text":"We talked to hundreds of experts\nin drug financing and venture capital."},{"time":423721,"text":"We talked to people\nwho have developed drugs."},{"time":425997,"text":"We talked to pharmaceutical companies."},{"time":427856,"text":"We actually looked at the data for drugs,"},{"time":430710,"text":"over 2,000 drugs that had been approved\nor denied or withdrawn,"},{"time":434906,"text":"and we also ran millions of simulations."},{"time":438230,"text":"And all that actually took a lot of time."},{"time":440784,"text":"But when we were done, we found something\nthat was sort of surprising."},{"time":444101,"text":"It was feasible to structure that fund"},{"time":445951,"text":"such that when you were done\nstructuring it,"},{"time":448067,"text":"you could actually produce low-risk bonds\nthat would be attractive to bond holders,"},{"time":452030,"text":"that would give you yields\nof about five to eight percent,"},{"time":454794,"text":"and you could produce equity"},{"time":456283,"text":"that would give equity holders\nabout a 12 percent return."},{"time":459002,"text":"Now those returns aren't going\nto be attractive to a venture capitalist."},{"time":462408,"text":"They want to make those big bets"},{"time":463965,"text":"and get those billion dollar payoffs."},{"time":465995,"text":"But it turns out there are lots of other\nfolks that would be interested."},{"time":469457,"text":"That's right in the investment sweet spot\nof pension funds and 401(k) plans"},{"time":473060,"text":"and all this other stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474687,"text":"So we published some articles\nin the academic press,"},{"time":477183,"text":"in medical journals, in finance journals."},{"time":482022,"text":"But it wasn't until we actually\ngot the popular press interested in this"},{"time":485491,"text":"that we began to get some traction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488360,"text":"We wanted to do more\nthan just make people aware of it."},{"time":490980,"text":"We wanted people to get involved."},{"time":492584,"text":"So we took all of our computer code\nand made that available online"},{"time":495721,"text":"under an open-source license\nto anybody that wanted it."},{"time":498433,"text":"And you guys can download it today"},{"time":500152,"text":"if you want to run your own experiments\nto see if this would work."},{"time":503303,"text":"And that was really effective,"},{"time":504812,"text":"because people that didn't\nbelieve our assumptions"},{"time":507200,"text":"could try their own\nand see how it would work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509375,"text":"Now there's an obvious problem, which is,"},{"time":511385,"text":"is there enough money\nin the world to fund this?"},{"time":513684,"text":"I've told you there's enough drugs,\nbut is there enough money?"},{"time":516625,"text":"There's 100 trillion dollars of capital"},{"time":518555,"text":"currently invested\nin fixed-income securities."},{"time":522632,"text":"That's a hundred thousand billion."},{"time":526320,"text":"There's plenty of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527951,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532088,"text":"But we realized it's more than\njust money that's required."},{"time":534855,"text":"We had to get people motivated, involved,"},{"time":536879,"text":"and get them to understand this."},{"time":538775,"text":"And we started thinking about all\nthe different things that could go wrong."},{"time":542334,"text":"What are all the challenges\nthat might get in the way?"},{"time":545220,"text":"And we had a long list."},{"time":546464,"text":"We assigned a bunch of people,\nincluding ourselves,"},{"time":549467,"text":"different pieces of this problem."},{"time":551910,"text":"And we said, could you start\na work stream on credit risk?"},{"time":554745,"text":"Could you start a work stream\non the regulatory aspects?"},{"time":557414,"text":"Could you start a work stream\non how you would manage so many projects?"},{"time":561471,"text":"And we had all these experts get together\nand do these different work streams,"},{"time":565167,"text":"and then we held a conference."},{"time":567039,"text":"The conference was held\nover this past summer."},{"time":569293,"text":"It was an invitation-only conference."},{"time":571097,"text":"It was sponsored\nby the American Cancer Society"},{"time":573371,"text":"and done in collaboration\nwith the National Cancer Institute."},{"time":576804,"text":"We had experts from every field\nwe thought would be important,"},{"time":579786,"text":"including the government, and people\nthat run research centers,"},{"time":582807,"text":"and for two days they heard the reports"},{"time":585268,"text":"from those five work streams,\nand talked about it."},{"time":587884,"text":"It was the first time the people\nwho could make this happen"},{"time":590746,"text":"sat across the table from each other\nand had these conversations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593837,"text":"Now these conferences,\nit's typical to have a dinner,"},{"time":597358,"text":"and at that dinner,\nyou get to know each other,"},{"time":600154,"text":"sort of like what we're doing here."},{"time":601919,"text":"I happened to look out the window,"},{"time":603589,"text":"and hand on my heart,"},{"time":604909,"text":"on the night of this conference --\nit was the summertime --"},{"time":607745,"text":"and that's what I saw, a double rainbow."},{"time":610013,"text":"So I'd like to think it was a good sign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612082,"text":"Since the conference, we've got people\nworking between Paris and San Francisco,"},{"time":616307,"text":"lots of different folks working on this"},{"time":618200,"text":"to try to see if we can\nreally make it happen."},{"time":620932,"text":"We're not looking to start a fund,\nbut we want somebody else to do this."},{"time":624359,"text":"Because, again, I'm not a scientist."},{"time":626553,"text":"I can't build a drug."},{"time":628456,"text":"I'm never going to have enough money\nto fund even one of those trials."},{"time":632443,"text":"But all of us together, with our 401(k)s,"},{"time":635292,"text":"with our 529 plans,\nwith our pension plans,"},{"time":637884,"text":"all of us together can actually\nfund hundreds of trials"},{"time":640791,"text":"and get paid well for doing it"},{"time":642399,"text":"and save millions of lives like my dad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645170,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646345,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}